				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p>I have detailed convervations with a friend of mine.  I believe that ADHD medication only works on a child who has ADHD.</p>
<p>There could be other factors that mimic ADHD.  One factor is a LD.  It could be anxiety.  It could be sensory.  It could also be vision.  A good book to read is &quot;The Out of Sync Child&quot; by Carol Kranowitz and &quot;When a child struggles;the Myth of 20/20 vision&quot; by Dr. David Cook.</p>
<p>My son had a detailed vision processing test which is a separate exam from standard eye tests.  My son had &quot;convergence insuffiencey&quot; and &quot;eye teaming&quot; problems, so the eyes are not in sync reading accross the page and makes him tired and rub his eyes.</p>
<p>He has vision therapy twice a week for 32 sessions.  Insurance pays for half and we pay out of pocket for the other half since it's educational related.  </p>
<p>I hope you can look into some of these other factors.  I am not aware that ADHD medication works on a child that doesn't have it.  Let us know how things go. </p>
																		<p class="hiddensignature">Annette</p>
